						<div class="postbody">It may be smart to include CRC checking.  There is a great XMODEM routine for 6502 by <a href="http://sbc.rictor.org/" class="postlink">Daryl Rictor</a>.  I've used with the Squeedo interface and also while bit-banging over the controller port.  It was rare, but every now and then I would see a retransmitted block.  XMODEM is just 128 bytes of data, with CRC-16.</div>

